76561198225098124,Recommended,250050,31455670,Posted: 29 April,all,Lord Ignus,"""If I have reached further than others, it is because I stood on the shoulders of giants."" If Netwon had played this game, the giants would be the bodies of your dead comrades.In this game, you control an army of knights in desperate search for the Cup of Life. However, it's a dangerous journey and many will die along the way. Fortunately, each knight has a better chance than the one before; not only because you've learned from his sacrifice, but because his body is now a helpful platform on top of those spikes, or is completing an electrical circuit to open that door, or is just enough a stool to help you reach that ledge. Jump, push, and die your way through 4 worlds full of puzzle-filled levels, leaving a huge body count in your wake.It's one of the most hilariously fun puzzle platformers I've ever played. Its gimmick seems like it would get old very quickly, but they keep finding new ways to keep it fresh and introduce new challenges. It's puzzles can be a bit on the easy side if you're a veteren at puzzle games, but the notion of having to die to progress adds a perspective of puzzle-solving not often seen in other games.All in all, it's a blast. A must-buy for platformer fans."
