76561198161422019,Recommended,250050,26139704,"Posted: 20 October, 2016",all,MalibuLizard,"I bought this because it was cheap and looked like a good game for when I'm in the mood to play something more casual. I was surprised by how fun this game got with each new level and each new mechanic. The gameplay is very addictive and simple yet tons of fun and thoughtful.The pacing is great as each level offers carefully constructed puzzles that feel fresh rather then copied or repeated. As you get used to encountering a trap or puzzle mechanic the game adds new layers to keep you thinking!l*] The game is plain fun. Not a single complaint about it. The gameplay is solid and feels rewarding as you solve silly puzzles by sacrificing your oddly named loyal knights.The audio is pleasant, no annoying soundtrack or repetitive horrible sound effects that drive you insane.The visual style and graphics suit the game completely and are quite delightful.Appeals to casual gamers as well as those looking for a challenge as each level can be replayed with several objectives to try and accomplish including finding secrets, beating a level with the fewest 'lives' sacrificed and speed running. Completing all challenges for each level and earning the highest score/award can be quite challenging even for a hardcore gamer- but these objectives are all optional and are NOT required to continue to the next level.The length of the game so far is quite a bit more then I originally expected. After 3 hours I don't think I'm even at the half way point yet- I might be nowhere near it!In my 3 hours I've expirienced no stutter, long loading times, bugs, glitches or any annoyances. The game has run quickly and smoothly throughout, and I'm playing it at it's highest settings on a fairly cheap laptop that can't run AAA games.I would recommend this game to anyone who wants a game that can be played in short bursts or longer sessions, anyone looking for something non-serious and affordable."
