76561198030367984,Recommended,250050,17937350,"Posted: 7 September, 2015",all,ExaltedDuck,"I would describe this as taking the Lost Vikings or Gobliins style sidescroller puzzle game motif and twisting through the lens of a little good old fashion Lemmings misantrhopy.  You have an unlimited number of lives, played a singly-control controlled knights making their way through the level toward a treasure.  As obstacles arise, you throw your knights at them in ways that invariably costs their lives in morbidly humorous ways to allow pasasage by their successors.  Each level also has par conditions to try to beat for time and lives spent and a hidden monster to feed a knight to for full completion.  The graphics and music are excellent.  The control is at times imprecise (for instance, using one knight as a platoform in a spike pit can be a bit finicky if it's not at a full-speed jump distance away) but manageable.  Good level design and a very charming style more than make up for it."
