,Recommended,250050,31554397,Posted: 5 May,all,Anorexic Penguin,"Great game. Overall, I'd give it a solid 8.5/10.The puzzles are actually challenging. Not to mention I absolutely adore the core mechanic (I mean, who heard of a game where you HAVE to die?!?); truly unique stuff. The puzzles require some thought, and you have multiple metrics on which you are graded, significantly increasing the replayability. Additionally, the game maintains an light, humorus tone (which is particually important, because if you mishandle the aesthetics on a game about killing yourself then it takes a dark turn mighty fast).Honestly, I don't see much room for improvement. I rate at an 8.5 because I reserve anything higher than that for games which take my breath away/bring a tear to my eye/engage me for a long time, and by design this just isn't one of those games. Not a complaint as much as an explanation.Kudos to the devs for making me laugh while I killed myself 10 times over."
